==文物古蹟==

===考古發掘===
{{see also|倫敦博物館|倫敦考古博物館}}
不少遺跡尚埋藏倫敦地底，但難以探知。綜觀倫敦的地質，由地層深部[[磚土|磚土]]、沙粒，以及倫敦黏土上的碎石組成。<ref>Grimes, [https://books.google.com/books?id=LhEcBQAAQBAJ&pg=PP22 Ch. I.] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LhEcBQAAQBAJ&pg=PP22 |date=20200805084947 }}</ref> 羅馬碎石路的特徵，在於碎石反復分層堆放，或碎石的跨度可追蹤至數個地點。木組件的微小殘餘物難以察覺。石建築或曾留下地基，但往往在[[中世紀|中世紀]]至[[近世|近世]]被拆除，石磈改用於大廣場的營建。<ref name=salis6/>

[[File:London_praetorium.jpg|thumb]]
[[File:St_Alphage_Garden_19.jpg|thumb]][[倫敦城牆|倫敦城牆]]遺址之一（今{{tsl|en|St Alphege London Wall||St Alphege Gardens}}）]]
針對羅馬倫敦的首份全面的考古學報告成於17世紀，1666年[[倫敦大火|倫敦大火]]後。[[建築師|建築師]][[克里斯多佛·雷恩|克里斯多佛·雷恩]]替{{link-en|盧德門山|Ludgate Hill}}（Ludgate Hill）上的[[聖保羅座堂|聖保羅座堂]]修繕時，並無發現支持[[William_Camden|Camden]]論點的記載。<ref>{{Citation | last = Camden | first = William | author-link = William Camden | title = [[Britannia_(Camden)|Britannia]] | place = London | publisher = G. Bishop & J. Norton | year = 1607 | pages = 306–7 | language = la}}</ref> <!--that it had been built over a Roman temple to the goddess [[Diana_(mythology)|Diana]].--><ref>{{cite book | last = Clark | first = John | chapter = The Temple of Diana| editor-last = Bird| editor-first = Joanna | editor2-last = Hassall | editor2-first = Mark | editor3-last = Sheldon | editor3-first = Harvey | display-editors=1 | title = Interpreting Roman London | publisher = Oxbow | series = Oxbow Monograph | volume = 58 | year = 1996 | location = Oxford | pages = 1–9}}</ref> 19世紀期間，乃至[[第二次世界大戰|第二次世界大戰]]中[[納粹德國|納粹德國]]策動的[[倫敦大轟炸|倫敦大轟炸]]之後，倫敦的大範圍重建考慮到古倫敦的大部分地區，加以紀錄和保護，同時帶來現代的更新。{{refn|[[伦敦文物学会|伦敦文物学会]]（Society of Antiquaries of London）的羅馬時期及中世紀倫敦考古發掘委員會（Roman and Medieval London Excavation Council）發掘出的當時倫敦市的爆炸點，相關的位置圖參見{{tsl|en|W.F. Grimes||Grimes}}。<ref name=grimy>{{cite book|last=Grimes|first=William Francis|authorlink=William Francis Grimes|title=The Excavation of Roman and Mediaeval London|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LhEcBQAAQBAJ&pg=PR2|chapter=Map of the walled city of London showing areas devastated by bombing, with sites excavated by the Excavation Council|publisher=Routledge|date=1968|isbn=1317604717|access-date=2015-08-11|archive-date=2020-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805165547/https://books.google.com/books?id=LhEcBQAAQBAJ&pg=PR2|dead-url=no}}</ref>}} <!--1848年，[[比靈斯門羅馬房屋|比靈斯門羅馬房屋]]（Roman house at Billingsgate）隨着{{link-en|倫敦煤交易所|Coal Exchange (London)}}（London Coal Exchange）的興建而被發現。1860年代，excavations by [[Augustus_Pitt_Rivers|General Rivers]] uncovered a large number of human skulls and almost no other bones 在{{link-en|瓦爾布魯克河|Walbrook}}床。<ref>Thorpe, Lewis. ''The History of the Kings of Britain'', p. 19. Penguin, 1966.</ref> The discovery recalls a passage in {{link-en|蒙默思的傑弗里|Geoffrey of Monmouth}}（Geoffrey of Monmouth）的[[野史|野史]]《{{link-en|不列顛諸王史|Historia Regum Britanniae}}》（拉丁文Historia Regum Britanniae，英文History of the Kings of Britain） where 阿斯克列庇歐多圖斯[[Julius_Asclepiodotus|Asclepiodotus]] besieged the last remnants of the [[Britannic_Empire|usurper]] [[Allectus|Allectus]]'s army at "Londonia". Having battered the town's walls with [[Roman_siege_engines|siegeworks]] constructed by allied Britons, Asclepiodotus accepted [[Livius_Gallus|the commander]]'s surrender only to have the [[Venedotia|Venedotia]]ns rush upon them, [[Celtic_decapitation|ritually decapitating]] them and throwing the heads into the river "Gallemborne".<ref name=herb>Galfredus Monumetensis [Geoffrey of Monmouth]. [http://books.google.com/books?id=LBw2AAAAMAAJ&pg=PA62 ''Historia Regnum Britanniae'' [''History of the Kings of Britain''], Vol. V, Ch. iv.] {{c.|1136}}. {{la icon}}</ref><ref name=herb2>[[Geoffrey_of_Monmouth|Geoffrey of Monmouth]]. Translated by J.A. Giles & al. as [[s:History_of_the_Kings_of_Britain/Book_5#4|''Geoffrey of Monmouth's British History'', Vol. V, Ch. IV]], in ''Six Old English Chronicles of Which Two Are Now First Translated from the Monkish Latin Originals: Ethelwerd's Chronicle, Asser's Life of Alfred, 蒙默思的傑弗里的英國史 Gildas, Nennius, and Richard of Cirencester''. Henry G. Bohn (London), 1848. Hosted at [[s:Main_Page|Wikisource]].</ref> Asclepiodotus's siege was an actual event that occurred in {{Smallcaps|ad}} 296, but further skull finds beneath the 3rd-century wall place at least some of the slaughter before its construction, leading most modern scholars to attribute them to [[布狄卡|布狄卡]]勢力.<ref>Merrifield, [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=39wl2I48e7kC&pg=PA57 p. 57.]</ref><ref>{{tsl|en|John Morris (historian)||Morris, John}}. ''Londinium: London in the Roman Empire'', p. 111. 1982.</ref> 1947年，城西北部的守兵要塞被發現。<ref>Grimes, [https://books.google.com/books?id=LhEcBQAAQBAJ&pg=PR2-IA2 Ch. II, §2.]</ref> In 1954, excavations of what was thought to have been an early church instead revealed the [[London_Mithraeum|London Mithraeum]], which was relocated to permit building over its original site. (The building erected at the time has since been demolished, but plans to return the temple to its former home have been blocked.) 1970年代，考古學家在不列顛尼亞行省的沿岸地點展開了密集的發掘，並無所獲。這些地點遍佈建築，不利於研究和新發現。<ref name=haverfield>Haverfield, p. 145</ref> 另一階段的考古工作隨着[[倫敦證券交易所|倫敦證券交易所]]1986年撤銷管制而進行。1991年以來，[[倫敦博物館|倫敦博物館]]考古部（Museum of London Archaeology Service, MOLAS）從事了許多考古發掘。2011年，該考古部的工作移交至獨立運作的{{link-en|倫敦考古博物館|Museum of London Archaeology}}（Museum of London Archaeology, MOLA），following legislation to address [[The_Rose_(theatre)|the Rose Theatre]] fiasco.-->

